50|$|<b>Difetarsone</b> {{often has}} minor side effects, which include rashes, nausea and vomiting. It has also {{resulted}} in angioedema {{in at least one}} known case.|$|E
50|$|Mebendazole is 90% {{effective}} in the first dose, and albendazole may also be offered as an anti-parasitic agent. Adding iron to the bloodstream helps solve the iron deficiency and rectal prolapse. <b>Difetarsone</b> is also an effective treatment.|$|E
50|$|<b>Difetarsone</b> is an {{antiprotozoal}} agent. Various {{studies have}} shown it to be particularly effective against Trichuris trichiura, {{commonly known as the}} whipworm. Prior to the drugs use in the early 1970s, there were few effective treatments for this infection. It has also been used to treat Entamoeba histolytica infections.|$|E

